/**
 * @page mastering_utility_wizard_impl Mastering Utility Wizard Implementations
 *
 * @brief Details for the implementation files used by the Mastering Utility Wizard.
 *
 * This page covers the command line wizard components that handle album and song
 * metadata editing before saving everything to a Markup file.
 *
 * @section cpp_impl Cpp Implementation
 * @subsection cpp_file File: cpp/wizard.cpp
 *
 * The Cpp version provides a command line interface for managing audio project
 * metadata. It uses the DConsole library to parse arguments and handle user prompts.
 *
 * Features include:
 * - Creating and editing album level metadata
 * - Adding or modifying songs in an album
 * - Setting fields such as title artist genre year copyright
 * - Defining file paths and FFmpeg args
 * - Loading existing Markup files
 * - Saving new or edited project data
 *
 *
 * @section rust_impl Rust Implementation
 * @subsection rust_file File: rs/wizard.rs
 *
 * The Rust version offers similar workflow and interactivity for album and song
 * metadata editing. It connects to the masteringutil core through the cxx crate
 * to access shared functionality.
 *
 * It includes custom prompting utilities and command line parsing for automation
 * and help output while keeping the workflow streamlined.
 */
